snippet.textDisplay: Its in a dialect which is a mix of assamese, hindi and their own adivasi language. This language is known as baganiya because it is spoken by the tea-pluckers of Assam. These people were brought from Central India to Assam by the British to work as tea garden labours.
snippet.textOriginal: Its in a dialect which is a mix of assamese, hindi and their own adivasi language. This language is known as baganiya because it is spoken by the tea-pluckers of Assam. These people were brought from Central India to Assam by the British to work as tea garden labours.

snippet.textDisplay: This language have it's origin from Chotanagpur Plateau ( mostly Jharkhand,  parts of Odisha, WB, Chattisgarh). It belongs to the Tribals community.  The language is commonly known with the name "Sadri" or "Nagpuri" in Jharkhand. The song would have been more amazing if emphasis is given to the Tribal instuments (like Mandal/ Mandar, Dholki, Nagada).
snippet.textOriginal: This language have it's origin from Chotanagpur Plateau ( mostly Jharkhand,  parts of Odisha, WB, Chattisgarh). It belongs to the Tribals community.
